column4: Review journal dedicated to developments in the field of molecular cell biology.
Forum for research on the location, diagnosis, and monitoring of inherited and infectious disease utilizing nucleic acid techniques.
Studies on the general organization and activity of cells from the molecular level to the level of cell interaction and differentiation.

Archives of abstracts since 1997, of the rapid communications of scientific investigation in chemical and biological research. Full text available to subscribers at Elsevier Science BV, The Netherlands.
Sample issue, and searchable archive of monthly abstracts since 1997, with PDF of articles available to subscribers. Includes instruction to authors and customer services at Nature, London, UK.

ECM offers free access to abstracts and full text in PDF of peer-reviewed papers. Provided as the official journal of Swiss Society for Biomaterials and Tissue and Cell Engineering Society. Includes online submission and related links.
Electronic journal, with original articles and reviews on stem cell research and ethics.

column3: Biochimica et Biophysica Acta Molecular Cell Research

Structural biochemistry of cells and tissues, a forum for the cytochemical and histochemical research community in the life sciences.

Publishes original findings and reviews concerning the structure and function of cells, organelles and macromolecular assemblies.
Papers covering all aspects of mechanisms, actions and structural components of cellular signalling systems.

column3: Current Advances in Cell & Developmental Biology

Articles related to the biochemical effects, synthesis and secretions of extracellular signals (hormones, and neurotransmitters) and to the understanding of cellular regulatory mechanisms involved in hormonal control.
Papers on the structure, function and macromolecular organization of cells and cell components focussing on cellular dynamics, motility and differentiation.
Covers a range of topics in contemporary cell biology. Published by The Company of Biologists Ltd.

Aims to stimulate both research on the basis of mechanisms of apoptosis and on its role in various human disease processes.

A central repository for information on both the infrastructure of cell technology and the applied use of cell cultures, thus providing a panoramic perspective of the many facets and disciplines needed to develop successful cell cultures. Available online.

A forum for publishing the most up-to-date methods developed during the course of cell science research involving vertebrates, invertebrates, plants or single-celled prokaryotic or eukaryotic organisms. Available online.
Articles concerning all phenomena related to cell motility, including structural, biochemical, biophysical, and theoretical approaches.
Embraces all aspects of analytical cytology: characterization and measurement of cells and cellular constitutents for biological, diagnostic, and therapeutic purposes.

Articles in all areas of eukaryotic cell biology and physiology: regulation of growth and differentiation by growth factors and cytokines, signal transduction by growth factors, cytokines and their cognate receptors.l
Quarterly journal publishing peer-reviewed papers on stem cells, germ line genetic engineering, tissue regeneration, transgenics and nuclear transfer.
Topics include cellular, biochemical and molecular aspects of gene structure and function, cell cycle, apoptosis and immunology.
Devoted to original research on the organization of cells, their components and extracellular products, at all levels including the grouping and interrelations of cells, in tissues and organs.

Journal devoted specifically to molecular histology and cell biology. Articles dealing with the localization and identification of molecular components, metabolic activities and cell biological aspects of cells and tissues.
Devoted to the advancement and dissemination of fundamental knowledge concerning the molecular biology of cells. Official publication of the Korean Society for Molecular Biology (KSMB).
Articles related to cell surface function - including biochemical genetics, development, pharmacology, endocrinology, and immunology. Available online.
Research in the fields of cellular and molecular genetics of higher eukaryotic systems.
Fundamental knowledge in the areas of bioenergetics, membranes, and transport, including oxidative phosphorylation, photosynthesis, muscle contraction, and biomembranes.

Research articles concerned with the analysis of neuronal and brain function at the cellular and subcellular levels.
Articles on basic cell biology along with physiological, pharmacological, and toxic response of cellular and subcellular systems.
Papers on the nature, the structure, genesis and functions of biological membranes, and on the physics and chemistry of artificial membranes with a bearing on biomembranes.

Study of cell physiology in space et the University of California Medical School and VA Medical Center, SF.

Pohang University of Science Technology, Dept. of Life Science Dr. Pann-Ghill Suh and Dr. Sung Ho Ryu.
Research on cell growth and division and key differentiation processes at MIT.
A Biomedical Technology Research Center supported by the National Center for Research Resources and National Institutes of Health for the study of viable systems.

Specialize in cell signaling, insulin, G protein-coupled receptors, and ubiquitines.

Protocols, publications, lab members and links at the Salk Institute, San Diego, California.

Research on motility through cross-disciplinary research, profiles of team members, postdoctoral opportunities, job openings at Perdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana.

Research on nucleocytoplasmic transport and the nuclear envelope at the Netherlands Cancer Institute, Amsterdam.
Phospho-specific Antibodies and other Innovative Discovery Tools for Cell Signaling Research.

For education and to organize cryonics in Canada. Does not provide cryonics services.

Ralph Merkle's cryonics introduction. Short but requires some knowledge of cryonics already.
CryoCare Foundation offers cryonics services. Includes an explanation of cryonics, with a library of articles.
A series of technical papers on cryopreservation research.

A cryonics public education organization in the Maryland/D.C. area. Not a service provider.

An on-line discussion group for those who are considering joining a cryonics organization but are worried about what their friends and family might think.

A long article by Terry Grossman, reprinted from The Babyboomers Guide to Living Forever (2000).
A non-profit organization that aims to educate and inform the general public about cryonics. Does not provide cryonics services and is not affiliated with any service organization.
Lively discussions of cryonics, cryogenics, cryobiology, life extension, transhumanism, death, and related issues.

A bit weird, since the Nederlands city government actively worked to oust Bredo Morstoel (the "frozen dead guy") from their town several years ago. But there he still sits, now the frozen centerpiece of a festival.
Site for information and discussion of cryonics in the United Kingdom. Provides standby assistance to its members who have signed up with a cryonics service provider.
Web site for James Halperin's 1998 SF novel, which explores the future of cryonics and nanotechnology.

column4: By R. Michael Perry, PhD. This book considers how the problems of death and the hereafter ought to be addressed in light of continuing scientific progress. Perry presents the cases for immortalism, cryonics, and even the possibility of resurrecting the dead through the creation of replicas.
Kenneth Starr vs. Clinton cartoon with cryonics theme. By John Bailey.
Two young ladies travel cross-country with the cryogenically frozen head of Walt Sidney. Not to be confused with Walt Disney. Stories, photos, and history.
Tongue-in-cheek news about staying young forever, faq, and cryonic warehouse.

An introduction by Canadian Ben Best, 8 printed pages.
The Cryonic's Institute's Introduction to Cryonics. 11 printed pages.
The why of cryonics, as understood by the Cryonics Institute.
An introduction by Jerry Emanuelson of Colorado Futurescience. 3 printed pages.
Heating/freezing stages for microscopy, covering the widest temperature range from -196?C to 1500?C.

Manufacturer and distributor of temperature-sensitive, frozen packaging containers for the shipping of biological items, especially the CryoPorter, for the safe transportation of semen and embryos at cryogenic temperatures. In Los Angeles, CA.

Suppliers of laboratory products and equipment for in vitro fertilization.

Tissue bank for sperm and embryo storage in Los Angeles and Palo Alto, California, and in Cambridge MA. Umbilical cord blood storage in Santa Monica, California.
